# Fashion Trend Analyzer

**[Try the live demo here](https://fashion-trend-analyzer.streamlit.app/)**

Fashion Trend Analyzer is an end-to-end pipeline for analyzing e-commerce fashion images. It scrapes product images, performs segmentation, builds image representations, clusters them into style groups, and generates natural-language summaries and keywords for each cluster.

The system has two pipelines:

* **Current (CLIP-based)**: Uses OpenCLIP embeddings + clustering + LLM labeling.
* **Legacy (Autoencoder-based)**: Uses a custom-trained convolutional autoencoder for latent feature extraction and clustering.

A **Streamlit dashboard** is included to visualize results.

---

## Project Structure

```
fashion_trend_analyzer/
├── src/                     # All scripts
│   ├── websraper.py         # Scraper for product images
│   ├── segment.py           # YOLO + SAM segmentation
│   ├── cluster_pipeline.py  # Current CLIP pipeline: embeddings + clustering
│   ├── old_cluster_pipeline.py  # Legacy autoencoder pipeline
│   ├── label_clusters.py    # Cluster labeling with OpenAI multimodal LLM
│   ├── dashboard.py         # Streamlit dashboard
│   └── autoencoder_train.py # Legacy file that trains the custom autoencoder
│
├── images/
│   ├── original_images/     # Scraped originals
│   ├── segmented_images/    # YOLO+SAM segmented items
│   └── clustered_images/    # Segmented items organized per cluster + labels.csv/json
│
├── models/                  # Models & weights
│   ├── sam_weights.pth      # Segment Anything (not included, large file)
│   ├── yolo_weights.pt      # YOLO checkpoint
│   ├── encoder.h5           # Legacy encoder (autoencoder)
│   ├── autoencoder.h5       # Legacy full autoencoder
│   └── best_autoencoder.weights.h5  # Legacy best weights from training
│
├── data/
│   ├── clip_embeddings.npy  # Embedding matrix (N x D)
│   └── clip_filenames.json  # Aligned filenames
│
├── logs/
│   ├── training_loss.png    # Legacy autoencoder training curve
│   ├── run_meta.json        # Run metadata
│   ├── autoencoder_history.json
│   └── autoencoder_summary.txt
│
├── deployment/
│   └── run_pipeline.sh      # Convenience script for full pipeline
│
├── requirements.txt
├── .gitignore
├── .env                     # Environment vars (API keys, etc.)
└── README.md
```

